<subSubSection id="C307E19DFFFE0B64FF4281DABA41F89D" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA2B216FFFE0B64FF4281DABB0AFEA7" blockId="6.[151,1437,151,321]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">
<emphasis id="B9696E04FFFE0B64FF4281DAB97EFF57" bold="true" box="[199,315,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1DC995FFFE0B64FEC681DABA5AFF56" baseAuthorityName="Fauvel" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[323,543,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Omalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picipenne">
<emphasis id="B9696E04FFFE0B64FEC681DABA5AFF56" box="[323,543,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">Omalium picipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described based on an unspecified number of 
<typeStatus id="54A60CB4FFFE0B64FB5681DABD70FF57" box="[1235,1333,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">syntypes</typeStatus>
from the unknown locality in 
<collectingCountry id="F30AF286FFFE0B64FE0181F6B981FF33" box="[388,452,187,213]" name="Chile" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">Chile</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CCFE7FFFE0B64FE5581F6BA97FF30" author="Coiffait, H. &amp; Saiz, F." box="[464,722,187,214]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" pagination="339 - 468" refId="ref4921" refString="Coiffait, H. &amp; Saiz, F. (1968) Les Staphylinidae (sensu lato) du Chile. In: Deboutteville, C. &amp; Rapoport, E. (Eds.), Biologie de Amerique Australe. Etudes sur la faune du sol. 4. Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique, Paris, pp. 339 - 468." type="book chapter" year="1968">Coiffait &amp; Saiz (1968)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed it as “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DC995FFFE0B64FC2F81F6BC6FFF33" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1940" box="[938,1066,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Omaliopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9696E04FFFE0B64FC2F81F6BC6FFF33" box="[938,1066,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">Omaliopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(?)”. I studied slightly damaged 
<typeStatus id="54A60CB4FFFE0B64FF128192B8ABFF1F" box="[151,238,223,249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">syntype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation id="1326AE93FFFE0B64FF7B8192B906FF1F" box="[254,323,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1854,1878]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,189,1818]" captionTargetId="figure-16@4.[152,1435,181,1830]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Habitus of species of Omaliini: 1—Omaliopsis russata (male, syntype), 2—O. russata (Chile, Aguas Calientes), 3—O. struyvei (holotype), 4—Stenomalium picipennis (syntype), 5—S. sp. (female; Chile, Corral), 6—Xenanthobium andicola (Chile, Corral). Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581688" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581688/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) and found that based on the shapes of the body and the maxillary palpomere, and the structure of the carinate mesosternum in the anterior portion, it belongs to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DC995FFFE0B64FC3B804EBD6DFEFB" authority="Blackwelder, 1943" authorityName="Blackwelder" authorityYear="1943" box="[958,1320,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenomalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9696E04FFFE0B64FC3B804EBC15FEFB" box="[958,1104,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">Stenomalium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CCFE7FFFE0B64FBD3804EBD6DFEFB" author="Blackwelder, R. E." box="[1110,1320,259,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" pagination="1 - 658" refId="ref4810" refString="Blackwelder, R. E. (1943) Monograph of the West Indian beetles of the family Staphylinidae. United States National Museum Bulletin, 182, i - viii + 1 - 658. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.182. i" type="journal article" year="1943">Blackwelder, 1943</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see other morphological details in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CCFE7FFFE0B64FE2B806ABA27FEA7" author="Bernhauer, M." box="[430,610,295,321]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" pagination="193 - 216" refId="ref4704" refString="Bernhauer, M. (1939) Neue Staphyliniden (Coleoptera) aus Neu-Seeland. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Seris 11, 4, 193 - 216. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222933908526985" type="journal article" year="1939">Bernhauer 1939</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CCFE7FFFE0B64FD1D806ABB07FEA7" author="Cameron, M." box="[664,834,294,321]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" pagination="779 - 793" refId="ref4860" refString="Cameron, M. (1945) Some observations on the Staphylinidae of the Broun Collection of Coleoptera in the British Museum, with descriptions of new genera and species. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 11, 11, 779 - 793. [1944] https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222934408527474" type="journal article" year="1945">Cameron 1945</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF62E29EFFFE0B64FF1284B7BBF2F9BC" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6581692" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6581692" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6581692/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" startId="6.[151,264,1530,1554]" targetBox="[157,1416,357,1493]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="8BA2B216FFFE0B64FF1284B7BBF2F9BC" blockId="6.[151,1436,1530,1627]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">
<emphasis id="B9696E04FFFE0B64FF1284B7B916F9F4" bold="true" box="[151,339,1530,1554]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">FIGURES 13–18.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1DC995FFFE0B64FEDD84B7BA64F9F4" authorityName="Shavrin" authorityYear="2022" box="[344,545,1530,1554]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Omaliopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="struyvei">
<emphasis id="B9696E04FFFE0B64FEDD84B7BA64F9F4" box="[344,545,1530,1554]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">Omaliopsis struyvei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(holotype): 13—aedeagus (parameral view), 14—aedeagus (lateral view), 15—male abdominal tergite VIII (dorsal view), 16—male abdominal sternite VIII (ventral view), 17—female abdominal tergite VIII (dorsal view), 18—female abdominal sternite VIII (ventral view). Scale bar: 0.10 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BA2B216FFFE0B64FF4287C4BA41F89D" blockId="6.[151,1436,1673,1915]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">
<taxonomicName id="4C1DC995FFFE0B64FF4287C4B91CF945" authorityName="Blackwelder" authorityYear="1943" box="[199,345,1673,1699]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenomalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9696E04FFFE0B64FF4287C4B91CF945" box="[199,345,1673,1699]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">Stenomalium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CCFE7FFFE0B64FD2187C4BB2BF945" author="Bernhauer, M." box="[676,878,1673,1699]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" pagination="193 - 216" refId="ref4704" refString="Bernhauer, M. (1939) Neue Staphyliniden (Coleoptera) aus Neu-Seeland. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Seris 11, 4, 193 - 216. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222933908526985" type="journal article" year="1939">Bernhauer (1939)</bibRefCitation>
, but he did not designate the 
<typeStatus id="54A60CB4FFFE0B64FB4487C4BCB4F945" box="[1217,1265,1673,1699]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">type</typeStatus>
spesies, so the name was unavailable (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CCFE7FFFE0B64FE2687E0BA01F921" author="Herman, L. H." box="[419,580,1709,1735]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref5109" refString="Herman, L. H. (2001) Catalogue of the Staphylinidae (Insecta: Coleoptera). 1758 to the end of the second millenium. Bulletion of the American Museum of Natural History, 265 (1 - 7), i - vi + 1 - 4218. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090.265.1.1" type="journal article" year="2001">Herman 2001</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CCFE7FFFE0B64FDDC87E0BB7FF921" author="Blackwelder, R. E." box="[601,826,1709,1735]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" pagination="1 - 658" refId="ref4810" refString="Blackwelder, R. E. (1943) Monograph of the West Indian beetles of the family Staphylinidae. United States National Museum Bulletin, 182, i - viii + 1 - 658. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.182. i" type="journal article" year="1943">Blackwelder (1943)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed it as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DC995FFFE0B64FB2987E0BD51F921" authorityName="Gravenhorst" authorityYear="1802" box="[1196,1300,1709,1735]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Omalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9696E04FFFE0B64FB2987E0BD51F921" box="[1196,1300,1709,1735]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">Omalium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, designated the 
<typeStatus id="54A60CB4FFFE0B64FF44879CB8B4F90D" box="[193,241,1745,1771]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">type</typeStatus>
species and therefore he is the author of this taxon (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CCFE7FFFE0B64FCC4879CBBA4F90D" author="Herman, L. H." box="[833,993,1745,1771]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref5109" refString="Herman, L. H. (2001) Catalogue of the Staphylinidae (Insecta: Coleoptera). 1758 to the end of the second millenium. Bulletion of the American Museum of Natural History, 265 (1 - 7), i - vi + 1 - 4218. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090.265.1.1" type="journal article" year="2001">Herman 2001</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CCFE7FFFE0B64FC70879CBCC5F90D" author="Steel, W. O." box="[1013,1152,1744,1771]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref5271" refString="Steel, W. O. (1960) A revision of the Phloeocharinae and Omaliinae of New Caledonia (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). Bulletin Institut royal des Sciences naturelles de Belgique, 36 (53), 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="1960">Steel (1960)</bibRefCitation>
elevated 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DC995FFFE0B64FB69879CBD3BF90D" authorityName="Blackwelder" authorityYear="1943" box="[1260,1406,1745,1771]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenomalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9696E04FFFE0B64FB69879CBD3BF90D" box="[1260,1406,1745,1771]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">Stenomalium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the genus level. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DC995FFFE0B64FEC987B8B99BF8E9" authorityName="Blackwelder" authorityYear="1943" box="[332,478,1781,1807]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenomalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9696E04FFFE0B64FEC987B8B99BF8E9" box="[332,478,1781,1807]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">Stenomalium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
contains 15 species, known from 
<collectingCountry id="F30AF286FFFE0B64FCDF87B8BBB5F8E9" box="[858,1008,1781,1807]" name="New Zealand" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F30AF286FFFE0B64FBA387B8BC96F8E9" box="[1062,1235,1781,1807]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CCFE7FFFE0B64FB6487B8B8B3F8D4" author="Klimaszewski, J. &amp; Newton, A. F. &amp; Thayer, M. K." pageId="6" pageNumber="180" pagination="143 - 160" refId="ref5173" refString="Klimaszewski, J., Newton, A. F. &amp; Thayer, M. K. (1996) A review of the New Zealand rove beetles (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). New Zealand Journal of Zoology, 23, 143 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03014223.1996.9518074" type="journal article" year="1996">
Klimaszewski 
<emphasis id="B9696E04FFFE0B64FA0D87B8B8E8F8D5" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">et al</emphasis>
. 1996
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CCFE7FFFE0B64FE848654B9D6F8D4" author="Thayer, M. K." box="[257,403,1816,1843]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" pagination="143 - 160" refId="ref5314" refString="Thayer, M. K. (1996) [Nomenclatural notes]. In: Appendix 1. Taxonomic changes to New Zealand Staphylinidae. In: Klimaszewski, Newton, and Thayer, A review of the New Zealand rove beetles (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). New Zealand Journal of Zoology, 23, pp. 143 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03014223.1996.9518074" type="journal article" year="1996">Thayer 1996</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CCFE7FFFE0B64FE1A8654BA79F8D5" author="Herman, L. H." box="[415,572,1817,1843]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref5109" refString="Herman, L. H. (2001) Catalogue of the Staphylinidae (Insecta: Coleoptera). 1758 to the end of the second millenium. Bulletion of the American Museum of Natural History, 265 (1 - 7), i - vi + 1 - 4218. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090.265.1.1" type="journal article" year="2001">Herman 2001</bibRefCitation>
). The genus requires revision because some species which were attributed to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DC995FFFE0B64FF128670B96CF8B1" authorityName="Blackwelder" authorityYear="1943" box="[151,297,1853,1879]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenomalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9696E04FFFE0B64FF128670B96CF8B1" box="[151,297,1853,1879]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">Stenomalium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may belong to other taxa (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CCFE7FFFE0B64FDDF8670BB3AF8B1" author="Klimaszewski, J. &amp; Newton, A. F. &amp; Thayer, M. K." box="[602,895,1852,1879]" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" pagination="143 - 160" refId="ref5173" refString="Klimaszewski, J., Newton, A. F. &amp; Thayer, M. K. (1996) A review of the New Zealand rove beetles (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). New Zealand Journal of Zoology, 23, 143 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03014223.1996.9518074" type="journal article" year="1996">
Klimaszewski 
<emphasis id="B9696E04FFFE0B64FC868670BB70F8B1" box="[771,821,1853,1879]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">et al</emphasis>
. 1996
</bibRefCitation>
). The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DC995FFFE0B64FB8A8670BCE4F8B1" authorityName="Blackwelder" authorityYear="1943" box="[1039,1185,1853,1879]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenomalium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9696E04FFFE0B64FB8A8670BCE4F8B1" box="[1039,1185,1853,1879]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="180">Stenomalium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded here from South America for the first time.
</paragraph>
